The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 March is 233,490 (26,911.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 March, there were 4,449 new confirmed cases (512.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 4,295 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (154 extra cases).
